<subSubSection type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="69" pageNumber="70">
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Camisiidae" genus="Heminothrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ornatissimus">Heminothrus ornatissimus</taxonomicName>
(Berlese, 1910)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="69" pageNumber="70">
<taxonomicName authority="Berlese, 1885" authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1885" class="Arachnida" family="Lohmanniidae" genus="Angelia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oribatida" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ornatissima">Angelia ornatissima Berlese</taxonomicName>
, 1910, p. 224, pl. 20 fig. 61.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="materials_examined">
<paragraph pageId="69" pageNumber="70">
The types of 
<taxonomicName authority="Berlese, 1885" authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1885" class="Arachnida" family="Lohmanniidae" genus="Angelia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oribatida" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ornatissima">Angelia ornatissima</taxonomicName>
(viz. the nos. 81/9, 15 from Lake City, Florida) are still present in the collection. The species certainly belongs to the genus 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Camisiidae" genus="Heminothrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Heminothrus</taxonomicName>
; the figure will probably be sufficient for purposes of identification. The length is 0.585-0.600, and the breadth 0.290 mm; according to Berlese the measurements are 0.650 X 0.330 mm, in which the hairs are possibly included.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="69" pageNumber="70">
I remark that Berlese (1913) did not mention the species as a representative of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Nothridae" genus="Nothrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Heminothrus">Heminothrus</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
